node.text: The largest of all the spaces we’re updating in the house, the informal living room was under utilized due to an awkward spatial plan that failed to give the room much purpose. Our goal for this space is to provide an inviting, lobby like feel with several sitting areas where resident members will gather between classes, before meals, and at the end of the day. Head to the blog for an even closer look at the changes we’re making to bring our vision to life!

node.title: Tri Delta Traditional // Our Plan for the Informal Living Room

node.text: Install day is just a few weeks a way! Today, we’re taking you through the changes we’re making in the Sunroom at our #trideltatraditional project to breath new life into the original, heavy & dark design. By pulling back and simplifying this space with a timeless color palette & classic finishes, we’re certain that this area will quickly become a favorite for all the member residents at the house.

node.text: We’ve received so many questions regarding the layout of our #sntrideltatraditional project, so today we are taking you through the entire space, room by room. Stay tuned for BIG improvements in the coming weeks and head to the blog to see our BEFORE images + all the inspiration we’re using for the project. Have a question about the changes we’re making? Ask away! 💕

node.text:
Follow along as Jesse takes us through the changes we're making to the Formal Living Room in our #SNTriDeltaTraditional project! Designing this space was all about pulling back and making use of classic materials & timeless style. Floor to ceiling custom millwork alongside white oak hardwood flooring give this living area the light & bright base it deserves. 
See more changes we're making to the formal living room on the blog! https://bit.ly/3fAEu04

node.title: Tri Delta Traditional Remodel | Formal Living Room Update

There's still time to enter our $1000 @bodinewhite launch giveaway, but not much! ⏰ You have until 11:59 PM CST TONIGHT to enter. Don't miss out on this fantastic giveaway! Head to our story for more information on how to enter!

node.text:
It's giveaway time, friends! We are so thankful for each and every one of you who have supported the launch of @bodinewhite. To celebrate & say thank you, we are giving away $1000 to scoutandnimble.com & a FREE 1-hour design consult with founder & principal designer, Jesse Bodine of @bodinewhite. 🎉⁠
⁠
Here’s how to enter: ⁠
1. Follow @bodinewhite & @scoutandnimble⁠ (must be following both accounts in order to win!)
2. Like THIS post (This is the only post associated with this giveaway, you must enter HERE.)⁠
3. Tag a fellow design-lover in the comments of THIS post!⁠
⁠
For an extra entry: Share this post to your story and tag @bodinewhite & @scoutandnimble! 💗⁠
⁠
It's just that easy! Entry for the giveaway ends 7/25 at 11:59PM CST. Winner will be announced on 7/26 at noon CST. Only available to US residents. ⁠
⁠
Once again, thank you so much for following along and supporting us on this incredible journey, we are so excited to see where this new path takes us!⁠
⁠
